Reconnaissance

Reconnaissance is the first phase of ethical hacking where publicly available information is collected about a target.

Passive Reconnaissance

Passive reconnaissance gathers information without directly interacting with the target system.

WHOIS

WHOIS provides domain registration details such as registrar, registration date, expiry date and name servers.

DNS

DNS translates domain names into IP addresses. Common records include A, MX, NS and TXT.

HTTP Security Headers

Security headers protect websites from attacks such as clickjacking and cross-site scripting.

robots.txt

robots.txt tells search engines which pages should or should not be crawled.

sitemap.xml

A sitemap lists website URLs to help search engines index pages efficiently.